# API Patterns

## API Class Structure

Use static class methods for API clients:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
export class ComplaintAPI {
  private static prefix = "complaints";

  static async getAll(params: ComplaintQueryParams = {}) {
    try {
      const response = await api
        .get(this.prefix, { searchParams: params })
        .json<PaginatedData<Complaint>>();
      return response;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Error retrieving complaints:", error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  static async getById(id: string) {
    try {
      const response = await api
        .get(`${this.prefix}/${id}`)
        .json<Complaint>();
      return response;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Error retrieving complaint:", error);
      throw error;
    }
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

Always wrap API calls in try-catch and log errors:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
static async delete(id: string) {
  try {
    await api.delete(`${this.prefix}/${id}`);
    return { success: true };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error deleting complaint:", error);
    throw error;
  }
}

// ❌ BAD
static async delete(id: string) {
  await api.delete(`${this.prefix}/${id}`);
  return { success: true };
}
```

## Query Parameters

Use searchParams for GET requests:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
static async getAll(params: QueryParams = {}) {
  const response = await api.get(this.prefix, {
    searchParams: params,
  }).json<PaginatedData<T>>();
  return response;
}

// ❌ BAD - Manual URL construction
static async getAll(params: QueryParams = {}) {
  const url = `${this.prefix}?page=${params.page}&limit=${params.limit}`;
  const response = await api.get(url).json<PaginatedData<T>>();
  return response;
}
```

## Type Safety

Always provide generic types for responses:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const response = await api
  .get("complaints")
  .json<PaginatedData<Complaint>>();

// ❌ BAD
const response = await api.get("complaints").json();
```

## API Organization

Group related endpoints in the same class:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Single class for VK API
export class VkApi {
  private static prefix = "parsers/vk";

  static async getGroups() { /* ... */ }
  static async createGroup(data: VkFormData) { /* ... */ }
  static async deleteGroup(id: string) { /* ... */ }
  static async updateGroupStatus(id: string, action: string) { /* ... */ }
}

// ❌ BAD - Separate functions
export async function getVkGroups() { /* ... */ }
export async function createVkGroup() { /* ... */ }
```
